str2: A woman, wife, my lady. Probably from the base of ginomai; a woman; specially, a wife.

str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Blood, literally, figuratively or specially; by implication, bloodshed, also kindred.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
Twelve; the usual way in which the Twelve apostles of Jesus are referred to. From duo and deka; two and ten, i.e. A dozen.
A year. Apparently a primary word; a year.

str2: To spend in addition. From pros and analisko; to expend further.
All, the whole, entire, complete. A primary word; 'whole' or 'all', i.e. Complete, especially as noun or adverb.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A primary word; life, i.e. the present state of existence; by implication, the means of livelihood.
A physician. From iaomai; a physician.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.

str2: To have strength, be strong, be in full health and vigor, be able; meton: I prevail. From ischus; to have force.
From the same as therapon; to wait upon menially, i.e. to adore, or to relieve.
